        },
        "description": {
          "value": "<div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>The tophet makes one Slam attack against a target it is grappling as it shoves the creature into its open, flame-filled belly. If the attack hits, the target is forced into the tophet's burning belly, and the grapple ends. While inside the belly, the target is &amp;Reference[condition=restrained], has three-quarters cover against attacks and other effects outside the belly, and it takes 14 ([[/damage 4d6 type=fire]]) damage at the start of each of its turns. A creature, including the target, can take its action to pull the target free from the belly by succeeding on a [[/save ability=strength dc=16]] check. The creature making the attempt takes 7 ([[/damage 2d6 type=fire]]) damage.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div>",
          "chat": ""
        },
